Audio Transcription Application

Overview

The Audio Transcription Application is an AI-powered tool that converts uploaded audio files into text. It uses React (Vite) for the frontend and Java Spring Boot for the backend, with OpenAI integration for seamless transcription.

Features

Upload audio files and transcribe them into text

User-friendly UI built with React and Vite

Backend API powered by Spring Boot

OpenAI integration for accurate transcription

Secure and scalable architecture

Prerequisites

Make sure you have the following installed before setting up the project:

Node.js (>= 16.x)

npm or yarn

Java 17 (or higher)

Maven (for Spring Boot dependencies)

PostgreSQL/MySQL (if using a database)

Installation and Setup

1. Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/AnkurSingh0509/Audio-Transcribe.git
cd Audio-Transcribe

2. Backend (Spring Boot) Setup

Navigate to the backend folder:

cd backend

Install dependencies and build the project:

mvn clean install

Configure database (optional):

Update application.properties if using a database:

spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/transcription_db
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=yourpassword

Run the Spring Boot application:

mvn spring-boot:run

Backend will be running on http://localhost:8080

3. Frontend (React Vite) Setup

Navigate to the frontend folder:

cd frontend

Install dependencies:

npm install  # or yarn install

Start the frontend development server:

npm run dev  # or yarn dev

Frontend will be running on http://localhost:5173

API Endpoints

1. Upload Audio for Transcription

POST /api/transcribe

Request: Form-data with audioFile

Response: Transcribed text JSON

2. Get Transcription History

GET /api/history

Response: List of past transcriptions

Deployment

Frontend: Can be deployed on Vercel, Netlify, or any static hosting

Backend: Can be deployed on AWS, Heroku, or any cloud provider

Database: Hosted on AWS RDS, PostgreSQL, or MySQL

